{
  "stem": "10588.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The story started when I was in Ciechanow, Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I lived-- in the same city lived my aunt, and her seven children, and her grandchildren, and in-laws.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The whole family, she came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was my mother's older sister.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ester Pazdziorek.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of my cousins, my cousin Gitel, was also born and raised in Ciechanow, Poland, and was named after the same great grandmother Gitel than I.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was eight years.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in 1934.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was born in April too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she went to join her boyfriend in which later became the same year her husband.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I mentioned--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Jerusalem, Palestine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They got married.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "None of the relatives of his family-- he was also from Ciechanow, Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She went in 1934.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when she left, we all cried, because we didn't know whether we'd ever see each other again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Unfortunately, Gitel is the sole survivor of her murdered family, I'm the sole survivor of my murdered family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not one single person on my mother's side that lived in Poland at the time when Germany invaded Poland has survived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm the only one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was fortunate enough that I survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was married.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I realized that the only way to combat death is to create more life and joy in us and around us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Started to build a family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was extremely thrilled when my first son was born the same year that the state of Israel in October.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The state of Israel was established May 14, 1948.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my son was born October 3, 1948.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, I wanted very much to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on my own, I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when finally, when the [INAUDIBLE] offer to take the survivors, they offer to bring me here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we left, and I had two children, two sons, in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I came here--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the children were born?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I came February 15, 1952.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I settled Philadelphia and lived here ever since.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Philadelphia, I gave birth to two more sons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My first son is Erland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was named after both my husband-- because my husband is the sole survivor of his family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So am I.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So his named for his father and my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So his Hebrew name is [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In Swedish, we lived in Sweden, called Erland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was my other son, was born also in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Jerry.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was born November 28, 1951.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he was named after my husband's brother, Jakov.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then we came to America.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And life is a whole series of choices.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We both knew we wanted to have a larger family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Both came from a religious background.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And after the Holocaust, it was extremely important for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I love children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I love people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I love life.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we had to decide what we want to do.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we decide that we want to have more children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "God was good to us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I gave birth to two more sons, Samuel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Since we didn't have a girl, so he was named after my mother and after my husband's mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My husband's my mother was Laja.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My mother's name was Simo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So he was named [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And English name, Samuel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I regret that I didn't call him Simha.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Now, I wish that I could give any other name, but it's already too late.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Because I realized I'm proud of who I am.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because I believe if you cannot be accepted for what you are, you sure will not be accepted for what you are not.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So I wanted to have the names.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then my son, our youngest son, Michael, was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I'm not going to go into the story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But both Michael and I were called a miracle, because I was extremely sick.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I almost died when I gave birth to him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But somehow, we survived, and everybody was amazed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And Michael is a beautiful young man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I made three nice bar mitzahs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The fourth bar mitzah, I said, I did for my friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Now I wanted to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "To Israel.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "If I lived from the gate of Auschwitz to go to Israel, 2,000 years, my people prayed next year in Jerusalem, and I was the lucky one, that I can go.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "So I want to go for all of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Especially, I found out that after the war, everybody was looking for everybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So on my father's side, his sisters survived because they were sent to USSR.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And because of that, they survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They only lost the youngest child, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But not because he was killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Because he died of starvation and sickness.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "But the rest survive, and they went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was when I went the first time I decided to go for my son's bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
